Build trixie-uefi sdcard image for roc-rk3328-cc:

Note: Keyboard needs to have usb extention plugin to usb3 socket.
      Plugin USB3 1TB SSD to top usb2 socket.

There is no edk2-rk3328, so we use fedora-40 as edk2-rk3328 to install debian-13.1.0-arm64-netinst.iso to roc-rk3328-cc.

cd ~/Downloads
wget https://archives.fedoraproject.org/pub/archive/fedora/linux/releases/40/Workstation/aarch64/images/Fedora-Workstation-40-1.14.aarch64.raw.xz
wget https://get.debian.org/images/release/current/arm64/iso-cd/debian-13.1.0-arm64-netinst.iso

wget http://http.us.debian.org/debian/dists/trixie/main/installer-arm64/current/images/netboot/debian-installer/arm64/linux
wget http://http.us.debian.org/debian/dists/trixie/main/installer-arm64/current/images/netboot/debian-installer/arm64/initrd.gz

cd ~/build-roc-rk3328-cc/trixie-uefi
Plugin sdcard to PC. 
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
sudo mkfs.vfat /dev/sda1
sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda2
sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda3
sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda
xzcat ~/Downloads/Fedora-Workstation-40-1.14.aarch64.raw.xz | sudo dd status=progress bs=4096 of=/dev/sda skip=256 seek=4096 count=415744 conv=notrunc,fsync
sudo e2fsck -f /dev/sda2
sudo resize2fs /dev/sda2
sudo mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
cd /mnt
sudo \rm -rf efi dtb-* init* lost+found symvers* System* vmlinuz* .vmlinuz* config* dtb
sudo 7z x ~/Downloads/debian-13.1.0-arm64-netinst.iso; sync;
sudo cp ~/Downloads/linux .
sudo cp ~/Downloads/initrd.gz .
sudo chmod 755 loader/entries
sudo chmod 755 loader/entries/*
sudo vi loader/entries/* ( change to
linux /linux
initrd /initrd.gz
delete options
)
cd
sync; sudo umount /mnt;
sudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
cd /mnt
sudo \rm -rf b* c* f* o* r* s*
cd
sync; sudo umount /mnt;
Eject sdcard from PC.

Install trixie to USB3 1TB SSD:
Plugin sdcard, USB3 1TB SSD  and ethernet cable to roc-rk3328-cc. Power on roc-rk3328-cc.

Set User name: linaro
Partition ( Manual, select USB3 1TB SSD, create empty yes, select free, auto partion, all, finish, Yes )
Select debian desktop and gnome in addition to ssh and standard system utilities.

Force GRUB to install to the EFI ( Yes )
Update NVMRAM to boot Debian ( Yes )
Power off roc-rk3328-cc when installation completed. Remove sdcard.

Plugin USB3 1TB SSD to PC.
sudo fdisk -l /dev/sda
sudo e2label /dev/sda3 rootfs
sudo blkid /dev/sda2 ( write down UUID )
sudo blkid /dev/sda3 ( write down UUID )
sudo mount /dev/sda3 /mnt
ll /mnt/boot
sudo touch /mnt/boot/grub/grub.cfg
sudo vi /mnt/boot/grub/grub.cfg ( delete everything, add
set timeout=5
set default="Boot UUID"
set menu_color_normal=white/black
set menu_color_highlight=white/green
set root=(usb0,gpt3)

menuentry "Boot UUID" {
    search --no-floppy --fs-uuid --set=root --hint='usb0,gpt3' b2501488-ca2f-4700-baa6-cc1a6b5dd377
    echo    'Loading Linux vmlinuz-6.12.48+deb13-arm64 ...'
    linux /boot/vmlinuz-6.12.48+deb13-arm64 root=LABEL=rootfs rootwait rw rootdelay=10
    echo    'Loading initial ramdisk ...'
    initrd /boot/initrd.img-6.12.48+deb13-arm64
}
)
change above UUID accordingly.
sync; sudo umount /mnt;
sudo mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
sudo vi /mnt/EFI/debian/grub.cfg ( change hd0 to usb0 )
sync; sudo umount /mnt;
Eject USB3 1TB SSD from PC.

Plugin sdcard to PC.
sudo ./mkuboot.sh
Eject sdcard from PC.

Plugin sdcard, USB3 1TB SSD and ethernet cable to roc-rk3328-cc. Power on roc-rk3328-cc.
Disable power saving, auto suspend and screen saver.
su -
usermod -aG adm,sudo,video linaro
sync
reboot

sudo apt install net-tools openssh-server pulseaudio-utils
sudo systemctl start ssh.service
sudo systemctl enable ssh.service
sudo ifconfig
df .
uname -a
lsb_release -a
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sync
free
Check if Debian is running UEFI mode:
ls /sys/firmware/efi

sudo apt install flex bison libelf-dev libssl-dev build-essential libncurses-dev git speedtest-cli glmark2-es2-wayland mpv ffmpeg python3-pip python3-setuptools chromium chromium-sandbox pandoc pavucontrol zip rfkill vlc vlc-plugin-video-output vsftpd

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select hdmi as default )

chromium -> youtube -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

Do follows on PC, then ftp swan.mp4 to roc-rk3328-cc.
(
git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4][protocol=https]+bestaudio[ext=m4a][protocol=https]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4 --postprocessor-args "-vf scale=1024:640 -r 10 -c:v libx264 -b:v 2M -c:a copy"
)

mpv --hwdec-auto-copy swan.mp4
ffplay swan.mp4
cvlc --gl=wgl --glconv=any swan.mp4

sudo vi /etc/apt/sources.list ( append non-free-firmware to 3 deb http )
sudo apt update
sudo apt install firmware-realtek
ls -la /lib/firmware/rtl_bt
sudo reboot

Plugin ASUS USB-BT500 bluetooth usb dongle to roc-rk3328-cc usb3 socket.
sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
